The Herald Herald Reporter Zanu PF will hold an ordinary session of the Politburo at the ruling party’s headquarters in Harare today. In a statement, Zanu PF national spokesman Cde Christopher Mutsvangwa said: The Secretary for Administration Cde Dr O.M. Mpofu wishes to advise all members that there shall be an ordinary session of the Politburo to be held on Saturday, 15 January 2022 at the home of the people’s revolution, Zanu PF headquarters commencing 1000hours. All members should be seated by 0945hours sharp. Some of the issues expected to be discussed are the post-mortem on the just ended provincial elections and preparations on the upcoming by-elections, among other issues.